html:
Verb[edit]

iacuī

  1. first-person singular perfect active indicative of iaceō
    1. "I have lain prostrate, I lay prostrate, I have lain down, I lay down; I have reclined, I reclined"
    2. "I have lain ill, I lay ill, I have been sick"
    3. "I have lingered, I lingered, I have tarried, I tarried"
    4. "I have been placed or situated, I have lain, I lay"
    5. "I have been low, flat or level"
    6. "I have lain still, I lay still"
    7. "I have lain dead, I lay dead"
    8. "I have lain in ruins, I lay in ruins"
    9. "I have hung down loose, I hung down loose"
    10. (of the face or eyes) "I have been fixed on the ground, I have been cast down"
    11. "I have been indolent, idle or inactive"
    12. "I have lain dormant or abandoned, I lay dormant or abandoned, I have been of no avail"
    13. "I have lain overthrown, I lay overthrown; I have been refuted; I have been despised"
    14. (of speech or language) "I have been languid, dull or lifeless"
